heet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2810%2F28%2F24%29&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io )

Those two brands will almost certainly be sold. There=E2=80=99s an argument=
 that Tapestry C.E.O. Joanne Crevoiserat should still try to create a large=
r group by acquiring other companies that are not competing in the accessib=
le-luxury handbag space. LVMH-owned Marc Jacobs, which Tapestry has looked =
at in the past, even though LVMH says it=E2=80=99s not for sale, wouldn=E2=
=80=99t work. Nor would independently owned Tory Burch=E2=80=94also not for=
 sale=E2=80=94which is obliterating the competition both at full-price but =
also at outlet, where it has supplanted Kate Spade New York.

Crevoiserat could go after a ready-to-wear brand like Khaite, which is smal=
l but pure luxury and currently backed ( https://puck.news/khaite-expectati=
ons/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2810%2F28%2F24%29&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io ) by a private equity owner. In the past, people have sugges=
