sletter_content/another-fashion-scandal-alos-qatari-connection-the-loewes-p=
uzzle-puzzle/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2810%2F28%2F24%29&ut=
m_source=3Dcustomer.io ) at a $10 billion valuation at the end of last year=
, would be an interesting addition. After all, Coach has succeeded because =
it=E2=80=99s offering something young people can relate to, and that=E2=80=
=99s exactly what has made Alo successful.

The problem with all those scenarios is that it=E2=80=99s very unlikely the=
 Tapestry board would be willing to give Crevoiserat, a C.F.O. by trade, an=
other cycle to get a deal like
that done when this one failed so miserably. Indeed, at this magnitude, fai=
led deals usually lead to fired C.E.O.s.

